this study is to show that the psychological and anthropological interpretations of Kant's pure philosophy are not convincing and at the same time to illustrate some connections between his critical and anthropological investigations by means of an analysis of the theory of the faculties.Against both a "transcendental psychological" and an "anthropological" reading, the book presents Kant's theory of the faculties as a constitutive part of his critical philosophy and shows that there is a close connection between Kant's pure philosophy and his moral aesthetic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 4aGeist. 4aKritische Philosophie. 4aVirtues, knowledge, critical philosophy. 4aWissen. 70(DE-601)1052676350(DE-588)4188037-7aVerstand2gnd 70(DE-601)1057353370(DE-588)4126046-6aMoralischer Sinn2gnd 70(DE-601)1062002320(DE-588)4045798-9aPhilosophische Anthropologie2gnd 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103705530 cprintz978311035002940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110351149423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110351149.jpg  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEB